Name: MAVEN
Description: The MAVEN class is the container for MAVEN mission-specific metadata elements.

Name: mission_phase_name
Description: The mission_phase_name attribute provides the mission-defined name of a mission phase.

Name: Cruise
Description: The period of observations during the MAVEN's flight from Earth to Mars.

Name: EM-1
Description: Extended Mission 1: The period of observations during the first extension of the MAVEN mission covering 2015-11-17T00:00:00 to 2016-10-01T00:00:00.

Name: EM-2
Description: Extended Mission 2: The period of observations during the second extension of the MAVEN mission covering 2016-10-01T00:00:00 to 2018-10-01T00:00:00.

Name: EM-3
Description: Extended Mission 3: The period of observations during the third extension of the MAVEN mission covering 2018-10-01T00:00:00 to 2019-10-01T00:00:00.

Name: EM-4
Description: Extended Mission 4: The period of observations during the fourth extension of the MAVEN mission covering 2019-10-01T00:00:00 to 2021-10-01T00:00:00.

Name: EM-5
Description: Extended Mission 5: The period of observations during the fifth extension of the MAVEN mission covering 2021-10-01T00:00:00 and extending indefinitely.

Name: Mars Orbital Insertion
Description: The period of observations during the MAVEN's entry into Mar's orbit.

Name: Prime Mission
Description: The period of observations during the primary objective of the mission.

Name: Transition
Description: The period of time when the spacecraft was changing from cruise to orbital operations. Also referred to as 'Comissioning'.

Name: spacecraft_clock_start_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of a time period of interest.

Name: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
Description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count attribute provides the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of a time period of interest. These may be provided either as SCLK string values, or as encoded double precision SCLK values.

Name: mission_event_time_start_count
Description: The mission_event_time_start_count attribute provides the mission event time value at the beginning of a time period of interest. These may be provided either as SCLK string values, or as encoded double precision SCLK values.

Name: mission_event_time_stop_count
Description: The mission_event_time_stop_count attribute provides the mission event time value at the end of a time period of interest.

Name: Parameter
Description: The Parameter class provides information about a specified data parameter.

Name: name
Description: The name attribute provides a word or combination of words by which the object is known.

Name: description
Description: The description attribute provides a statement, picture in words, or account that describes or is otherwise relevant to the object.

Name: value
Description: The value attribute provides a single, allowed numerical or character string value.
